    {
      "type": "thought",
      "text": "The user has provided an image of a Windows Blue Screen of Death (BSOD) with the stop code `WHEA_UNCORRECTABLE_ERROR`. They want me to investigate the root cause, provide a fixability score (they mentioned \"ifix\" which I believe refers to iFixit's repairability score concept), discuss reliability, and suggest ways to improve PC temperature and component health without stress testing. They also want me to use PowerShell or Python tools to ensure these work.\n\nSince I'm in read-only mode, I can only search, read, and plan. I cannot run any commands or modify files. I need to gather information first.\n\nFirst, I should understand the error. `WHEA_UNCORRECTABLE_ERROR` is a hardware-related error in Windows. It indicates that the Windows Hardware Error Architecture (WHEA) has detected an uncorrectable hardware error. This could be due to CPU issues, RAM problems, motherboard failures, overclocking instability, overheating, or power supply issues.\n\nThe user mentions they've had this at least a couple of times yesterday. They want a proper enterprise root cause analysis. I should search for information about this error and common fixes. I'll use websearch to get more details.\n\nAlso, they want a fixability score using \"ifix\" – I think they mean iFixit's repairability score. I need to interpret that as a score from 1 to 10 indicating how easy it is to fix the issue.\n\nThey also ask about reliability and whether they can spend time improving PC temperature, and ensure all components are okay but without stress testing. They want a decent assessment using PowerShell or Python tools.\n\nSince I cannot run tools, I need to provide a plan. I should suggest diagnostic steps using built-in Windows tools (like Event Viewer, Windows Memory Diagnostic, etc.) and possibly PowerShell commands to check system health. Also, recommend monitoring temperatures with tools like Core Temp or HWMonitor.\n\nLet me start by searching for information about WHEA_UNCORRECTABLE_ERROR root cause analysis.",
